-- Fielmann May Expand Retail Chain by 200 Stores, CFO Tells Euro am Sonntag
-- B y   A n d r e a s   C r e m e r
-- 2010-10-09T16:23:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-09/fielmann-may-expand-retail-chain-by-200-stores-cfo-tells-euro-am-sonntag.html
Fielmann AG , Europe’s largest chain
of opticians, may expand by up to 200 stores in coming years,
 Euro am Sonntag  reported, citing Chief Financial Officer  Georg Alexander Zeiss .  Fielmann aims to increase the number of stores in Germany
and neighboring countries such as Austria and Poland to as many
as 850 over the next five to seven years from 650 now, Zeiss
said in an interview with the newspaper. The company also has a
franchise partner in the Baltic states, the CFO said, citing
“high demand” for optical products across Europe.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Andreas Cremer  in Berlin at 
 acremer@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editors responsible for this story:
Kenneth Wong at   kwong11@bloomberg.net . 